🌾 Smart Kisan

Smart Kisan is a simple web app we built to help farmers make better decisions using basic data like soil, weather, and crop choice.

The main idea is very straightforward:
👉 instead of taking risks in real life, farmers should be able to test their decisions first.

🚀 Why we built this

In many places, farming decisions are still based on experience and assumptions. That works sometimes, but with changing weather and soil conditions, it’s becoming risky.

Some common problems we noticed:

Farmers don’t always know their soil condition clearly
Weather is unpredictable
Fertilizers are often used without proper guidance
Choosing the wrong crop can lead to loss
There’s no way to “try before you plant”

We wanted to build something that reduces this uncertainty.

💡 What Smart Kisan does

The app lets users enter a few simple inputs:

Soil type
pH value
Rainfall level
Crop

Based on that, it gives:

Estimated yield
Cost and profit
Better crop suggestions
Fertilizer advice
Basic weather insights
🔥 What makes it different
🧪 Strategy Comparison (What-if)

Instead of showing just one result, the app compares:

Low investment
Balanced
High investment

So users can see which approach works best.

🧠 Decision Support

It doesn’t just give data — it tells you which option is better and why.

📊 Learning from past data

We store previous inputs and use them to generate simple insights like:

“In similar conditions, wheat gave better results.”

🛠️ Tech we used

We kept the stack simple so we could focus on the idea:

Frontend: React
Backend: Node.js + Express
Database: MongoDB
🔗 APIs used
Open-Meteo → weather data
data.gov.in → crop market prices
Nominatim (OpenStreetMap) → location detection
Twilio / WhatsApp API → notifications
